What an exciting time for Ted=E2=80=99s campaign.=09

Friend,=09=09=09=09=09=09

What an exciting time for Ted's campaign!

First, Ted travelled the state to help local Democratic candidates get out 
the vote ahead of Tuesday's 2015 election. It sure paid off: Democrats now 
run nine of Ohio's ten largest cities and all of the top five. And Ted had 
fun along the way too! Here are some of our favorite -- and most adorable -
- volunteers from the Team Ted GOTV Tour:

Then, yesterday on MSNBC with Steve Kornacki, Ted made clear to the nation 
that he intends to win one of the five seats that's necessary for Democrats
 to regain control of the Senate, so that he can help the middle class.

And before I forget, here's my favorite picture of all: Me with my best fri
end on National I Love You Day:

Ted has been devoted to the people of Ohio for more than 30 years. And as y
ou can see, he's more ready than ever for the challenge ahead. Ted has been
 to more than 40 counties across Ohio in the last few months alone - and I'
m right behind him with 39 under my belt and counting!

Everywhere I go, I see enthusiasm and excitement. It reminds me of the kind
 of grassroots movement that took off behind Ted's first congressional camp
aign. Then, just like now, we didn't have the most money, but we had the be
st message and it spread like wildfire through the people of Ohio. It's goi
ng to take that same kind of grassroots movement to get Ted elected this ti
me around. And it starts with you.

With just one year until Election Day, it would mean so much to him to know
 he has your friendship and support.

Will you sign our one year out card to Ted and tell him you're "all in" fro
m now until Election Day?

www.tedstrickland.com/all-in

He would love hearing from you and knowing that you are "in" for the challe
nge ahead. Every movement starts with just one person. I'm asking you to be
 that person for Ted today, so he can go to the U.S. Senate and fight for e
veryday working people here in Ohio.

Thank you so much,

Frances
